               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1348" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1348" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1348" type="surname" value="DAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1348" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>HANNAH DAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of George Day, of Denmark-street, St. George's-in-the-East. About ten o'clock in the evening of the 9th of April, I was standing at a picture shop—I saw a little boy by my side, and a boy behind me—I had a little child with me—I lifted her up to show her the pictures—I had 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and a penny in all in my pocket—I had one half-crown and 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I felt my pocket robbed, and I heard the other boy say to the prisoner, "Come on, it is all right"—there were others about, but no one could have taken my money but those two—they both ran off together—I ran, till I fell down, and could not run any further—this is my purse and money—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1349" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1349" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1349" type="surname" value="BURGESS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1349" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL BURGESS</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner going along the street, and the prosecutrix running after him, calling, "Stop thief"—I stopped him—he said, "I have got nothing," and as soon as he made use of those words he dropped some coppers down an area—I did not see the purse found—I took the prisoner to the station-house.</p>
               <p>
